
                                Dotfiles


Description
-----------

This is a collection of my personal dotfiles which I use on my own
machine.  They still have much room for improvement as I only created
them quite recently. Everything in them has come from other dotfiles I
have seen, online tutorials, personal research and some experimentation.
They will likely be very preferential, so the settings I have may not
appeal to everyone.


Installation
------------

Clone the repository locally into a dotfiles directory using:

        git clone git://github.com/kwyse/dotfiles.git ~/dotfiles

Create symlinks as follows:

        ln -s ~/dotfiles/vimrc ~/.vimrc

This will create a symlink for the vimrc file in the dotfiles directory
in the home directory, as this is where Vim expects the file to be
located. Do the same for the remaining files, substituting in the
different filenames.

The install.sh script is a simple bash script that would in theory do
all of this for you, but it is still a work in progress and has not been
tested, hence its use is not recommended.

